                <h2>Rotation</h2>
                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Activate Dark Shroud before combat</strong> &mdash; Gain shadow charges for damage reduction. This provides your primary defensive layer before engaging enemies.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Build Combo Points with basic attacks</strong> &mdash; Use your basic attack a few times to generate 3 Combo Points. This sets up maximum damage on your next Heartseeker cast.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Spam Heartseeker at max range</strong> &mdash; Your primary action. Fire seeking arrows that automatically track enemies. Stay at maximum range for Aspect of Retribution bonus crit.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Use Dash to maintain distance</strong> &mdash; Reposition constantly to avoid melee enemies. Dash away when enemies get close, maintaining safe firing distance.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Shadow Step for emergency escapes</strong> &mdash; If caught in melee or CCed, use Shadow Step to teleport behind an enemy and gain Unstoppable. This breaks CC and repositions you safely.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Pop Shadow Clone during boss fights</strong> &mdash; Use your Ultimate during high-value targets to double your damage output. The clone mimics all your Heartseeker casts for massive burst.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Concealment as last resort</strong> &mdash; If overwhelmed, use Concealment to go invisible and break targeting. Reposition to a safe distance before re-engaging.</p>
